<font color="#FF0000">TO DR. SPATZ..................</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb 16 22:11:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dr. Spatz,<br><br>
&quot;Arthur - your hell is your own invention,&quot;<br><br>
Dr. Spatz, you know better than that. Now it is I who will tell you to cut the bullshit. That is about the most sadistic comment that can be said to anyone. I am talking about my feelings, regardless of their origin. Furthermore, until you get into my head, there is no way you can possibly know what is invention or real. With that logic, I can just hear you counselling a rape victim, or a victim of other violence. (Perhaps holes should be drilled in their heads to let it all run out?) For many, and on many levels, the Vietnam experience had very profound effects. I suggest you stop the overlay of your personal mechanistic bias and look at feelings.  <br><br>
&quot;fueled by lies, deceptions, and the trust you had in your government. Your government abandoned you the first day you went in country. It was your fellow soldiers that kept you alive, not your government.&quot;<br><br>
I agree with you, really, I do! <br><br>
&quot;I don't understand how you can get upset about someone breaking the law&quot;<br><br>
&quot;when the entire viet nam tragedy was the ultimate lawless act.&quot;<br><br>
The two topics are not connected. I am upset with those who permitted amnesty. I could care less about those who ran away. They are not an issue with me. See my post to Nurse Ratchet above.<br><br>
There are many &quot;ultimate&quot; lawless acts. They are always judged in the context of the observer. Many things judged good or evil are good or evil depending on the point of view from which they are observed.<br><br>
Your *opinion* is that the Vietnam War was the ultimate lawless act. The &quot;fact&quot; of it can never be determined as an absolute truth, so don't try to pedantically offer it as one. Remember, the closer you look at something, the less you often learn. That's a paradoxical truth of the universe.<br><br>
Personally, I feel my whole experience sucked, left me really badly screwed up for the past 26 years, it screwed up my family to boot, and I don't like it one bit. The &quot;ultimate lawless act&quot; has absolutely no meaning in my dealing with those personal issues. It offers no consolation or formula for a panacea.<br><br>
Feelings are often irrational, but very, very, real....and reality is where its at, isn't it?<br><br>
Regards,<br><br>
Arthur<br><br>

